{{Infobox ethnic group | group = Malaysians of Gujarat origin | image = | population = More than '''31,500''') <small>(>1% of Malaysian Indians)</small><ref>{{cite web|title=Gujarati of Malaysia|url=http://www.peoplegroups.org/Explore/groupdetails.aspx?peid=20235|website=PeopleGroups.org|accessdate=1 March 2017}}</ref> | popplace = {{flag|Malaysia}} ([[Peninsular Malaysia]]) | langs = [[Gujarati language|Gujarati]], [[Malaysian English|English]] and [[Malaysian language|Malaysian]] | rels = Predominantly [[Hinduism]]{{·}}[[Jainism]] {{hlist|Also: [[Christianity]]{{·}}[[Islam]]{{·}}[[Parsi]] }} | related = [[Tamil people|Tamil]], [[Tamil Malaysian]], [[Indian Singaporeans]], }}
'''Gujrati Malaysian''' are people of full or partial [[Gujarat]]i descent who were born in or immigrated to [[Malaysia]]. The community arrived to Malaya during 14 century to trade spices with [[Sultanate of Malacca]].<ref name="pressreader.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.pressreader.com/malaysia/the-sun-malaysia/20150225/281831462182561|title=PressReader.com - Connecting People Through News|website=Pressreader.com|accessdate=23 November 2017}}</ref> But, only during the 19th century this community settled in Malaysia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gujaratikl.com.my/general_info3.htm|title=Gujarati's Of Malaysia Welcome you ALL|website=Gujaratikl.com.my|accessdate=23 November 2017}}</ref> Most of this community work as traders. The Gujaratis were mainly from the ports of Cambay, Kutch and [[Surat]] in India and settled in urban part of Malaya like [[Georgetown, Penang|Georgetown]], [[Kuala Lumpur]] and [[Ipoh]].<ref name="pressreader.com"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.penangstory.net.my/indian-content-paperjessica.html|title=The North Indians - Rediscovering Roots in Penang|date=11 August 2015|website=Penangstory.net.my|accessdate=23 November 2017}}</ref>
