{{Infobox language |name=Labrador Inuit Pidgin French |altname=Belle Isle Pidgin |region=[[Straits of Belle Isle]] |era=late 17th century until ca. 1760 |familycolor=Creole |family= [[Pidgin|French Pidgin]] |iso3=none |glotto=bell1264 |glottorefname=Belle-Isle Pidgin }}
'''Labrador Inuit Pidgin French''', also called '''Belle Isle Pidgin''', was a [[French language|French]]-lexified [[pidgin]] spoken between [[Breton people|Breton]] and [[Basque people|Basque]] [[fishermen]] and the [[Inuit]] of [[Labrador]] from the late 17th century until about 1760.
